During the process of filming and editing @scum.line I wanted to move away from home for a couple of months so I could stay focused for finishing the film. I would hunker down for 8-12 hours a day just staring at a computer screen. Definitely needed to stretch my legs and get a mental break each day

For about a half out or so I would catch the sunset and turn a few laps at the house I was staying at. 

@rodrigosnaps came over one night when @joshtwelker and I were ripping and grabbed some photos with is film camera. Photos turned out so cool. Such a fun evening. 

The biggest shout out to @2312_bellz and @_jenna_bellz for giving me a place to live and work for a few months. #bestlandmatesever

🔑 Got the KEYS 🔑 
The Maur Compound 

It’s been a dream of Ally and I to one day own property. We never knew where or when we would ever have a chance to own land, but that was a goal. Our journey has taken us to Redding California 10 minutes from lake Shasta on a 5 acre lot. Location location location.

Our plan is to turn this in to the ultimate compound and place to raise our little groms. Home is where you make it and we are digging our roots in here. GOD is great. 

Let the Demo begin 💪🏽
@allymaur
The season is coming… juiced for it.

Maur Compound update 

6 weeks of progress

A cold but fun morning with the @fatsacwake crew on the delta.  Through some sacs in the @mbboats boat and got after it with @canevariphoto and @wandermanmedia floating in the water. Good times with good people. Stoked for the season to get going.

Smackin lips 

#feedthesoul #freeride
I look up to @joshtwelker riding a lot. He always seems to get his but super close to the board mid trick. Im stoked on this screener mid 3. Had to focus on my inner Twelker vibes for this one. 🤘🏽

It’s one of those huck it and go tricks. Switch has got me feeling all backwards in the air. It’s cause I’m a little nervous throwing it everytime that it’s one of my favorites tricks to stick. 

New angles with @wandermanmedia at the @fatsacwake shoot this year. 
.
Big wakes = more fun

@trevermaur + Slater = 🔥Father-Son Duo 

Shoutout to all the amazing dads out there! To our Team Hyperlite Dads, you are the epitome of coolness and the ultimate role models. From teaching us how to ride our first wakeboard, we couldn’t ask for better dads! Check out the full film on our YouTube 🎥

One of the heaviest spots I’ve taken on. 

Good buddy @codybenj hits me up and says I got you a spot. No questions, I was out there with a crew. Never walked it prior to bringing the crew. Much bigger in person then what the photos or google earth shows. She’s a massive drop. 

Once I laid eyes on this I knew it had potential to be an opener or closer spot for my @scum.line section… let the battle begin. 

100% one the most mentally challenging spots I’ve hit. It’s a blind Ollie. Meaning I couldn’t see any steps until after I initiated the 270. On top of that, there was a metal bean running the length in the landing zone which I would hit each fall. This was one of those spots where each time I had to walk to the top to try again I was in a whole different battle with my headspace. 

Can’t thank the crew enough for making it possible and giving me the stoke needed to give this beast multiple attempts. @joshtwelker @hayden_berg @codybenj 

Best feeling in the world when you overcome something that freaks ya out. 

If you havn’t checked out @scum.line Go Give It  Watch. Poured our hearts into this project 🤘🏽

Nothing better then getting our little humans out on the water. Lil man Otto was a champ. Just cruising. No crying, just chill and relaxed.

Huge thanks to @mbboats for keeping wakeboarding alive in the Maur household.

@heatwavevisual with the drop! The all new VECTOR designed by ya boy @acesanders I saw him wearing A rendition of these last September and I thought they were dope, he told me they were not finished. Almost a year later looks like these bad boys are out. It’s cool to see people care about the product they put out. Shades are sick! You guys crushed it! 🤙🏽

The adventures with Slay continues with 2 strokes and old school skis. I have vivid memories as a kid of when my dad @moman5373 would take me out on his race ski, now it’s my turn to pass those memories along. @kawasakiusa

2024 @hyperlitewake gear just dropped! BluePrint Loaded looking so fresh and so clean. 

Can’t say enough great words about the shape and construction of this board. It’s the most free and smooth edge to edge board I’ve ever gotten my hands on. If your looking for the best of the best… loaded is the way. 🤘🏽🤘🏽

#hyperlite #wakeboards #freeridemore #freeride #blueprint #scumline

A good friend of mine once told me that grabbing your board isn’t everything, that sometimes it’s just the way you get into positions. That’s been instilled into the way I ride everyday. Thanks @rodrigosnaps 🤘🏽 you’ve been not only a photographer to me but a a ton of wisdom throughout my wakeboard journey. Wouldn’t be where I am today with out our friendship. 

I encourage every fellow shredder out there to take a set and not grab anything and just poke everything out. It’s so dang fun! 

ABSOLUTELY love my 2024 @hyperlitewake blueprint graphic. Had a huge had in this graphic and it’s even better looking in real life then it is on the phone screen. 

#freeridemore

🚨VOTE NOW🚨@alliancewake less than 5 lines are LIVE. Check out all the lines from the contest. If your digging my line, send me a vote. LINK IN MY STORY

My whole mindset on this contest wasn’t to do the “best” 5 tricks in a row but to link 5 tricks together seamlessly that I felt would flow. I wanted my run to look like a complete soul sesh.

@mikeschwenne always told me that you should think of your riding like painting a picture. The trick might be the main piece but the rest of your ride is just as important to the painting. 

Thanks for putting on another less than 5 @alliancewake | love this contest

voting is still going. If your digging my take on the @alliancewake less than 5 contest then send some votes my way. 

LINK IN MY STORY to vote

#keepitswaggy #freeridemore

MoonRocks, NV

I used to be pretty intimidated with big bikes. Couple years ago I threw my leg over my buddies 250 @2312_stephen for the first time in the desert and that was it. Found myself a new hobby. Totally hooked. Been trying to get as much seat time as I can in the off season and I feel like I learn a ton each time. I have a long way to go to feel comfortable and confident but in time that will come. It’s sick to have a hobby to excel in each time you do it. Stoked on the moto. 🤘🏽
